<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-08T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-08T01:00:00-05:00" n="483" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 Chiang Kai-shek/7–849:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-08T15:00:00+09:00">July 8,
                                    1949—3 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 8—7:51 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>274. Chen Cheng<note n="54" xml:id="d483fn54">Governor of Taiwan
                                (Formosa).</note> yesterday told Steele, <hi rend="italic">Herald
                                Tribune</hi>, [that] Generalissimo<note n="55" xml:id="d483fn55">Chiang Kai-shek, who retired as President of the Republic of China
                                on January 21, 1949.</note> will go Canton next week to develop
                            solidarity on basis recent manifesto. May go inland after Canton. Chen
                            stated past defeats not due lack armies or matériel but lack will to
                            fight. Foresees resurgence national spirit through Generalissimo’s
                            efforts. Sent Canton 117, repeated Secretary of State 274.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>